joiner-mover-leaver.md

## Identity Lifecycle Management

### Joiner

- Manager put in a request or manager approval to onboard user 

- User created via IAM

- Assigned role based on department

- Assign birthright access only

- MFA enforced on first login

### Mover

- New manager must approve the new role old manager have to sign off 

- Role access reviewed and updated

- Previous permissions removed

- Change documented for audit purposes

### Leaver

- Access disabled immediately <1 Hour of termination 

- Keys and tokens revoked

- User removed from all groups

- Immediate notification via HRIS intergration 

- Audit Archival in referance SEC Rule 17a-4 or SOC2 requirements 
